---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import FirmwareInstaller from '../components/FirmwareInstaller.astro';
import VersionPicker from '../components/VersionPicker.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Install"
  description="Step-by-step instructions to install and update Q-Tune firmware using a Chrome browser and USB-C data cable. Connect your device, run the installer, and update your DIY guitar tuner pedal to the latest version."
>
  <h3>Requirements:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Chrome Web Browser</li>
    <li>USB-C Data Cable</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="not-prose">
    <VersionPicker
      directory="public/assets/install/artifacts"
      manifestPrefix="/assets/install/artifacts/manifest-"
      minVersion="2.6.8"
    />
  </div>

  <p>Release notes and discussion about firmware updates can be found on the <a href="https://forum.pedalpcb.com/threads/software-firmware-updates.26469/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PedalPCB forum</a>.</p>

  <h3>Instructions:</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Plug in Q-Tune to your computer using a USB-C data cable and then click the <strong>Connect to device</strong> button.</li>
    <li>If your computer recognizes the Q-Tune, it will show up as an option starting with <strong>USB JTAG/serial...</strong>.</li>
    <li>Select that option and click the <strong>Connect</strong> button.</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Install Q-Tune</strong> option.</li>
    <li><strong>DO NOT</strong> select the <strong>Erase device</strong> option unless you want to erase all of your user settings.</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Next</strong> button and then confirm by clicking the <strong>Install</strong> button.</li>
    <li>Wait for the installer to finish. Once it's done you can unplug the USB-C cable and put Q-Tune to use on your pedalboard!</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>First install of v5.0 or newer</h3>
  <p>
    Q-Tune v5.0 added support for two different boards. The first time you install
    v5.0 or newer, or any time you do a factory reset, your tuner shows a setup screen
    with two options: <strong>Solderless</strong> (the standard Q-Tune) and
    <strong>Thru-Hole</strong> (the Q-Tune Solder Kit). You only choose once.
  </p>
  <div class="not-prose my-6 rounded-lg border border-amber-glow/40 bg-amber-glow/10 px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-text-body">
      <strong class="text-text-heading">Choose carefully.</strong> The GPIOs that
      drive the relays and switches are reversed between the two boards. If you pick
      the wrong one, bypass and switching won't work correctly. Pick
      <strong>Solderless</strong> for the standard kit, or <strong>Thru-Hole</strong>
      if you soldered the board together from loose components.
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <FirmwareInstaller manifest="" />
</PageLayout>

<script is:inline defer src="/assets/install/js/main.js"></script>
